Updated review:  Got in touch with the Marketing Director, and HotBox really tried hard to make things right.  The amount of in-store credit was doubled and a full refund issued.  This local franchise screwed things up, but this incident doesn't seem to be indicative of how HotBox as a whole operates.  Original review:  They were out of hand-tossed and hippie crusts and only had thin crust available.  We ended up with a "pizza" with burnt edges and burned sauce.  Called to complain but gave us "the oven only had one setting" excuse.  The manager reluctantly offered a $10 in-store credit (our order totaled around $40).

I’ve always enjoyed Hot Box Pizza. Our crew was directing traffic near their location in West Lafayette. Our agents were told to make sure delivery drivers were not delayed.  Several staff members from that location chipped in and delivered a delicious pizza to our crew working in the rain. Hot pizza on a cold rainy night hitthe spot. Their kindness was greatly appreciated.  I visited the store this evening to pick up dinner and expressed my gratitude to the employees. All good guys.  Thanks Hot Box!!!
